    "created_at": "2025-10-07T03:28:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-10-07T03:36:07Z",
    "body": "Since Starship isn't the only one with this issue I had some fun with GTP5 to write a go CLI that does just that for any sort of configs. It's been working pretty nicely. Shameless plug, check it out: https://nekwebdev.github.io/confb\n\nIt does glob pattern, merges, for a few different formats.\n\nHere is my `~/.config/confb/confb.yaml` config for starship:\n\n```yaml\nversion: 1\n\ntargets:\n  - name: starship\n    format: toml\n    output: ~/.config/starship.toml\n    sources:\n      - path: ~/.config/starship-base.toml\n      - path: ~/.config/starship-colors.toml\n```",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
